    "recap_headline": "Long Beach State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "BAKERSFIELD, Calif.\n\u2014 Long Beach State was limited to six hits Friday night as Cal\u00a0State\u00a0Bakersfield claimed a 3-0 win in the series opener, snapping the Dirtbags' three-game winning streak and handing them their first shutout loss of the 2026 season.\nLong Beach State threatened in the first when\nJake Evans\ndoubled to right-center with one out, but Cal State Bakersfield's starter Ryan King stranded him there with consecutive outs to end the inning. In the bottom half, the Roadrunners took advantage of a leadoff walk, and a failed pickoff attempt that moved Jacob May into scoring position. Devon Wilkes drove in the game's first run with a groundout to second before Elgin Bennett added a two-out solo home run to right field for a 2-0 lead.\nThe Dirtbags created one of their best scoring chances in the third when\nConner Stewart\nsingled, advanced on\nTy Borgogno's\nsacrifice bunt and moved to third on\nTrevor Goldenetz's\nsingle to center. Goldenetz then stole second to put two runners in scoring position, but King escaped with back-to-back strikeouts to keep Long Beach State off the board.\nLong Beach State put two aboard again in the fourth when\nMatt Toomey\nsingled down the left-field line and\nAaron Perez\nfollowed with a single to right field, but Bakersfield ended the inning with a pickoff at first base before the Dirtbags could capitalize.\nOn the mound,\nCaleb Anderson\nkept the Dirtbags within reach through 6.2 innings. The right-hander allowed three runs on seven hits while generating 10 ground-ball outs. Cal State Bakersfield added its final run in the fifth after Evan Cloyd doubled to right-center and Wilkes followed with a two-out RBI double down the left-field line to make it 3-0.\nLong Beach State's final push came in the seventh when\nMatt Toomey\nwas hit by a pitch to open the inning and moved to second after\nConner Stewart\nreached on a shortstop error following\nAaron Perez's\nflyout to center. With two aboard and one out, Cal State Bakersfield turned to Jacob Gutierrez out of the bullpen, and after\nReid Montgomery\nlifted a sacrifice\u00a0fly ball to center, Gutierrez struck out\nTrevor Goldenetz\nswinging to end the game.\nGoldenetz led the Dirtbags with two hits, while Evans, Toomey, Perez, and Stewart each added one.\nTyler Gebb\nadded one scoreless inning\u00a0with two strikeouts and no hits allowed in relief, while the Dirtbags also cut down a runner at home in the seventh to keep the deficit at three.\nLong Beach State will continue the series Saturday against CSU Bakersfield, with first pitch set for 4 p.m. on ESPN+.",
